<h3>Overview</h3>
<p>
privacyIDEA is installed with a default configuration for users and administrators.
privacyIDEA provides a web UI, where normal users and administrators can login.
</p>
<p>
Users can login with their username and their domain password.
</p>
<p>
Administrators need to login with <em>&lt;adminname&gt;@admin</em> and their domain password, to get administrative rights.
</p>
<p>
At the command line the tool <em>pi-manage.py</em> can be used to manage additional administrators that are independent of the LDAP directory.
</p>
<p>
privacyIDEA uses MySQL to store the token information and
the Apache webserver to provide a management UI and a REST API.
</p>
<p>Public documentation can be found
<a href="http://privacyidea.readthedocs.org">here</a></p>

<h3>First steps</h3>
<p>You can now start to enroll tokens for the users. You can read
<a href="http://privacyidea.readthedocs.org/en/latest/firststeps/token.html">here</a>,
how to enroll a Google Authenticator App to users.</p>

<h3>Applications</h3>
<p>You can use privacyIDEA, to add a second factor when login in to your existing applications increasing security dramatically:
<ul>
<li>Local login or <b>SSH</b> to your <b>UCS Systems</b> using <em>privacyidea-pam</em>.</li>
<li>Local login to your <b>Windows Clients</b> using <em>privacyIDEA Credential Provider</em>.</li>
<li>Login at web applications like <b>OTRS</b> using corresponding <em>plugins</em>.</li>
<li>Login to <b>OpenVPN</b> using <em>privacyidea-pam</em>.</li>
</ul>
</p>

<h3>Open Source</h3>
<p>
privacyIDEA is a free project. Feedback, requests and proposals help to go on with the development. Post feedback at 
<a href="https://github.com/privacyidea/privacyidea">Github</a> as an issue or on the 
<a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/privacyidea">Google group</a>.
</p>
